msgid fraggren_txt {
text "_Technical Specifications: AEMG M80 Fragmentation Grenade

CLASSIFIED LEVEL YELLOW

PHALANX Extraterrestrial Response Unit

Technical Document, Delta Clearance

Filed: 20 March 2084

By: Cdr. Paul Navarre, R&D: Engineering Division, PHALANX, Atlantic Operations Command



Overview

The M80 Fragmentation grenade is produced by AEMG industries. Standard composition includes a safety-pin and handle, a timed fuse and an explosive charge, which are held within a fragmentation matrix composed of steel pellets and polymer.


Recommended Doctrine

The fragmentation pellets contained within the device have a relatively low armor penetrating capacity and are most effective when used against unarmoured aliens. The M80 model is considerably heavy and has a 7 meter radius of effect."
}

msgid fraggren2_txt {
text "_Technical Specifications: AEMG M82 Fragmentation Grenade

CLASSIFIED LEVEL YELLOW

PHALANX Extraterrestrial Response Unit

Technical Document, Delta Clearance

Filed: 21 March 2084

By: Cdr. Paul Navarre, R&D: Engineering Division, PHALANX, Atlantic Operations Command



Overview

The M82 Fragmentation grenade is produced by AEMG industries. It is a revised model of the predecessor M80 series. 
Standard composition includes a safety-pin and handle, a timed fuse and an explosive charge, which are held within a fragmentation matrix composed of steel pellets and polymer. 
The handle and surface texture have been revised, which combined with it's lighter weight, allows for an increased throwing range.


Recommended Doctrine

The fragmentation pellets contained within the device have a relatively low armor penetrating capacity and are most effective when used against unarmoured aliens. The M82 model is lighter than M80 and has a 6 meter radius of effect."
}

